com.wm.xmldata

Class XmlNamespaceMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
        • com.wm.xmldata.XmlNamespaceMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>

    public class XmlNamespaceMap
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
    This class maintains a mapping between prefixes and namespace URIs. It is similar to HashMap but requires a one-to-one relationship between prefix (key) and namespace (value). Any attempt to add an entry that includes a key (prefix) or value (namespace URI) that is already in use results in an error. An additional method putValue() generates a unique prefix. An additional method removeValue() allows a declaration to be removed without knowing the prefix.

      • putValue

        public java.lang.String putValue(java.lang.String namespace)
        Adds the namespace declaration using a unique generated prefix. The base prefix is established by the constructor call to XmlNamespaceMap. Each unique prefix is created by assigning an incrementing suffix of 1, 2, 3 ... etc. to the generated prefix.
        Parameters:
        namespace - the XML namespace
        Returns:
        the assigned prefix
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the namespace URI is already present as a value.
